  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "An 84-year-old man comes to the emergency department because of lower back pain and lower extremity weakness for 3 weeks. Over the past week, he has also found it increasingly difficult to urinate. He has a history of prostate cancer, for which he underwent radical prostatectomy 8 years ago. His prostate-specific antigen (PSA) level was undetectable until a routine follow-up visit last year, when it began to increase from 0.8 ng/mL to its present value of 64.3 ng/mL (N &lt; 4). An MRI of the spine shows infiltrative vertebral lesions with a collapse of the L5 vertebral body, resulting in cord compression at L4–L5. The patient receives one dose of intravenous dexamethasone and subsequently undergoes external beam radiation. Which of the following cellular changes is most likely to occur as a result of this treatment?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Formation of pyrimidine dimers"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Disruption of microtubule assembly"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Intercalation of neighbouring DNA base pairs"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Generation of hydroxyl radicals"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Formation of DNA crosslinks"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 4,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z0103f08b74140f5cced570a65cfa6093\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z0103f08b74140f5cced570a65cfa6093\" data-section-id=\"YzXnr00\">Nonionizing radiation</a> (e.g., UV radiation) causes covalent binding between adjacent <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=oo001S&anker=Zf0b129c1baa685598c8a918cd7fcf8f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"oo001S\" data-anker=\"Zf0b129c1baa685598c8a918cd7fcf8f3\" data-section-id=\"wLch-10\" data-sememe-id=\"6CXjGZ0\">pyrimidines</a>, leading to dimer formation (most commonly <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=oo001S&anker=Z92fa00bdace6fc23f6a42ba17c9f84a1\" data-learningcard-id=\"oo001S\" data-anker=\"Z92fa00bdace6fc23f6a42ba17c9f84a1\" data-section-id=\"wLch-10\" data-sememe-id=\"yJbd9u\">thymine</a> dimers). These dimers create bulky helix distortions, impairing normal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=oo001S&anker=Z68d825eaf9f4ef0d00ef8c2edb04382d\" data-learningcard-id=\"oo001S\" data-anker=\"Z68d825eaf9f4ef0d00ef8c2edb04382d\" data-section-id=\"CLcq-10\">base pairing</a> during replication, which increases the risk of developing mutations. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z0103f08b74140f5cced570a65cfa6093\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z0103f08b74140f5cced570a65cfa6093\" data-section-id=\"YzXnr00\">Nonionizing radiation</a> is not used for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=L50wkg&anker=Z06f7ff49cb23a87e0491ea5a638bcbdc\" data-learningcard-id=\"L50wkg\" data-anker=\"Z06f7ff49cb23a87e0491ea5a638bcbdc\" data-section-id=\"-n1DDh0\" data-sememe-id=\"IVbYDs\">external beam radiation</a> therapy for cancer; rather it is the causative agent for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\">skin</a> cancers.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_578de863b6638.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>UV light (abbreviated as h×ν) causes damage to the DNA, most commonly by dimerisation of adjoining thymine bases: the C=C double bonds are coupled to form a cyclobutane ring (red). A thymine dimer immediately interrupts DNA replication.</p></div></div></div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4m03fg&anker=Z50cce8f9d38eee7b6f71a6d51c071e4c\" data-learningcard-id=\"4m03fg\" data-anker=\"Z50cce8f9d38eee7b6f71a6d51c071e4c\" data-section-id=\"OW1Ilf0\" data-sememe-id=\"oka0Kk\">Vinca alkaloids</a> (e.g., <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4m03fg&anker=Zd81f442fc4204146e3dc72044029e13d\" data-learningcard-id=\"4m03fg\" data-anker=\"Zd81f442fc4204146e3dc72044029e13d\" data-section-id=\"OW1Ilf0\" data-sememe-id=\"RMblo8\">vincristine</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4m03fg&anker=Z6e31828e8352d4c097df63c0a37d58aa\" data-learningcard-id=\"4m03fg\" data-anker=\"Z6e31828e8352d4c097df63c0a37d58aa\" data-section-id=\"OW1Ilf0\" data-sememe-id=\"6kajKk\">vinblastine</a>) are <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4m03fg&anker=Z4c7ae79c18cb3c2f3e1fa98185b2d78d\" data-learningcard-id=\"4m03fg\" data-anker=\"Z4c7ae79c18cb3c2f3e1fa98185b2d78d\" data-sememe-id=\"ifbJNG\">chemotherapeutic agents</a> that disrupt <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Lo0wcS&anker=Ze5f7ee56e0fca05cfe183570be1173eb\" data-learningcard-id=\"Lo0wcS\" data-anker=\"Ze5f7ee56e0fca05cfe183570be1173eb\" data-section-id=\"GLcB_10\" data-sememe-id=\"Fpbgru\">microtubule</a> assembly by binding to β-<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Lo0wcS&anker=Ze730a3934cfe762dfa1259dd2c5f1718\" data-learningcard-id=\"Lo0wcS\" data-anker=\"Ze730a3934cfe762dfa1259dd2c5f1718\" data-section-id=\"GLcB_10\" data-sememe-id=\"RSXlzx\">tubulin</a>. This disruption prevents the formation of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Mo0McS&anker=Z8f44bf343a8b3ff53d54ef6349935678\" data-learningcard-id=\"Mo0McS\" data-anker=\"Z8f44bf343a8b3ff53d54ef6349935678\" data-section-id=\"dLco910\" data-sememe-id=\"lJbv8u\">mitotic spindle</a>, causing <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Mo0McS&anker=Za5444ddbd046f772b1023e469381a0be\" data-learningcard-id=\"Mo0McS\" data-anker=\"Za5444ddbd046f772b1023e469381a0be\" data-sememe-id=\"hJbcFu\">cell cycle</a> arrest. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4m03fg&anker=Z50cce8f9d38eee7b6f71a6d51c071e4c\" data-learningcard-id=\"4m03fg\" data-anker=\"Z50cce8f9d38eee7b6f71a6d51c071e4c\" data-section-id=\"OW1Ilf0\" data-sememe-id=\"oka0Kk\">Vinca alkaloids</a> are most commonly used to treat solid tumors, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=iT0Jq2&anker=Zc0da5e32087bb9fdebbaad4515b11425\" data-learningcard-id=\"iT0Jq2\" data-anker=\"Zc0da5e32087bb9fdebbaad4515b11425\" data-section-id=\"Hl0KyT\" data-sememe-id=\"vMbAq8\">leukemias</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z2586a20a2f640af294a4d86b9f8439d0\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z2586a20a2f640af294a4d86b9f8439d0\" data-section-id=\"azXQr00\" data-sememe-id=\"7RX4oB\">lymphomas</a>.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_5ea995082b7e4.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>Overview of common chemotherapeutic agents and their molecular targets.</p></div></div></div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4m03fg&anker=Z4fc06350709e29146df239d62114ec9b\" data-learningcard-id=\"4m03fg\" data-anker=\"Z4fc06350709e29146df239d62114ec9b\" data-section-id=\"NW1-lf0\" data-sememe-id=\"kkamLk\">Anthracyclines</a> (e.g., <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4m03fg&anker=Z755638f42b12fb67ef41212a511c5970\" data-learningcard-id=\"4m03fg\" data-anker=\"Z755638f42b12fb67ef41212a511c5970\" data-section-id=\"NW1-lf0\" data-sememe-id=\"OkaILk\">doxorubicin</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4m03fg&anker=Z0a3b9fc8e3bf1a227dbdc2c587d9c296\" data-learningcard-id=\"4m03fg\" data-anker=\"Z0a3b9fc8e3bf1a227dbdc2c587d9c296\" data-section-id=\"NW1-lf0\" data-sememe-id=\"lkavLk\">daunorubicin</a>) are <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4m03fg&anker=Z4c7ae79c18cb3c2f3e1fa98185b2d78d\" data-learningcard-id=\"4m03fg\" data-anker=\"Z4c7ae79c18cb3c2f3e1fa98185b2d78d\" data-sememe-id=\"ifbJNG\">chemotherapeutic agents</a> that destroy cells through intercalation between neighboring <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=oo001S&anker=Za0493ec3415ed9dd482e76317fbd9b9a\" data-learningcard-id=\"oo001S\" data-anker=\"Za0493ec3415ed9dd482e76317fbd9b9a\" data-section-id=\"DLc1-10\" data-sememe-id=\"Xqb9Cu\">DNA</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=oo001S&anker=Z68d825eaf9f4ef0d00ef8c2edb04382d\" data-learningcard-id=\"oo001S\" data-anker=\"Z68d825eaf9f4ef0d00ef8c2edb04382d\" data-section-id=\"CLcq-10\">base pairs</a>. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=oo001S&anker=Za0493ec3415ed9dd482e76317fbd9b9a\" data-learningcard-id=\"oo001S\" data-anker=\"Za0493ec3415ed9dd482e76317fbd9b9a\" data-section-id=\"DLc1-10\" data-sememe-id=\"Xqb9Cu\">DNA</a> intercalation leads to double-strand breaks and impaired replication. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4m03fg&anker=Z4fc06350709e29146df239d62114ec9b\" data-learningcard-id=\"4m03fg\" data-anker=\"Z4fc06350709e29146df239d62114ec9b\" data-section-id=\"NW1-lf0\" data-sememe-id=\"kkamLk\">Anthracyclines</a> also inhibit <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ko0U1S&anker=Zf5cd3679b2c0ed00bca0f7bddc7052c0\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ko0U1S\" data-anker=\"Zf5cd3679b2c0ed00bca0f7bddc7052c0\" data-section-id=\"_Lc5ZW0\" data-sememe-id=\"8dXO7C\">topoisomerase II</a>, which prevents repair of coil relaxation and is lethal to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Lo0wcS&anker=Z0b2dbba84cd425084862e30873efee1a\" data-learningcard-id=\"Lo0wcS\" data-anker=\"Z0b2dbba84cd425084862e30873efee1a\">the cell</a>. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4m03fg&anker=Z4fc06350709e29146df239d62114ec9b\" data-learningcard-id=\"4m03fg\" data-anker=\"Z4fc06350709e29146df239d62114ec9b\" data-section-id=\"NW1-lf0\" data-sememe-id=\"kkamLk\">Anthracyclines</a> are most commonly used for solid tumors, including <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=B60zMS&anker=Z1b473b16a0c304b8376bbf09eefde16e\" data-learningcard-id=\"B60zMS\" data-anker=\"Z1b473b16a0c304b8376bbf09eefde16e\">breast</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=nh07ef&anker=Z3ff7ac92fae21c5ca2363549c47bb7e7\" data-learningcard-id=\"nh07ef\" data-anker=\"Z3ff7ac92fae21c5ca2363549c47bb7e7\" data-sememe-id=\"sk0t6T\">lung cancer</a>, as well as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=iT0Jq2&anker=Zc0da5e32087bb9fdebbaad4515b11425\" data-learningcard-id=\"iT0Jq2\" data-anker=\"Zc0da5e32087bb9fdebbaad4515b11425\" data-section-id=\"Hl0KyT\" data-sememe-id=\"vMbAq8\">leukemias</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z2586a20a2f640af294a4d86b9f8439d0\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z2586a20a2f640af294a4d86b9f8439d0\" data-section-id=\"azXQr00\" data-sememe-id=\"7RX4oB\">lymphomas</a>.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_5ea995082b7e4.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>Overview of common chemotherapeutic agents and their molecular targets.</p></div></div></div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) CORRECT:</h4>\n<span class=\"wichtig\"><b><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Zc4389e9049b53cade58fa5f794deed44\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Zc4389e9049b53cade58fa5f794deed44\" data-section-id=\"YzXnr00\" data-sememe-id=\"_dX5sC\">Ionizing radiation</a></b></span> (e.g., gamma <span data-sememe-id=\"ta1Xm20\">irradiation</span>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=in0JGg&anker=Zf22a2d04575027ccbd9bc2a111f58066\" data-learningcard-id=\"in0JGg\" data-anker=\"Zf22a2d04575027ccbd9bc2a111f58066\" data-sememe-id=\"eK0x2S\">x-ray</a>) causes ionization of the water component of cells and the resultant generation of<span class=\"wichtig\"><b> hydroxyl radicals</b></span>. Hydroxyl radicals are a type of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=VP0GdT&anker=Z51158cb80b552a12e27be5f3a026d8f7\" data-learningcard-id=\"VP0GdT\" data-anker=\"Z51158cb80b552a12e27be5f3a026d8f7\" data-section-id=\"Ea18m20\" data-sememe-id=\"UYXbo9\">reactive oxygen species</a> that attack the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=oo001S&anker=Za0493ec3415ed9dd482e76317fbd9b9a\" data-learningcard-id=\"oo001S\" data-anker=\"Za0493ec3415ed9dd482e76317fbd9b9a\" data-section-id=\"DLc1-10\" data-sememe-id=\"Xqb9Cu\">DNA</a> backbone and bases. These reactions cause <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=oo001S&anker=Za0493ec3415ed9dd482e76317fbd9b9a\" data-learningcard-id=\"oo001S\" data-anker=\"Za0493ec3415ed9dd482e76317fbd9b9a\" data-section-id=\"DLc1-10\" data-sememe-id=\"Xqb9Cu\">DNA</a> single-strand breaks and, most deleteriously, <span class=\"wichtig\"><b><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=oo001S&anker=Za0493ec3415ed9dd482e76317fbd9b9a\" data-learningcard-id=\"oo001S\" data-anker=\"Za0493ec3415ed9dd482e76317fbd9b9a\" data-section-id=\"DLc1-10\" data-sememe-id=\"Xqb9Cu\">DNA</a> double-strand breaks</b></span>, which are very difficult for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Lo0wcS&anker=Z0b2dbba84cd425084862e30873efee1a\" data-learningcard-id=\"Lo0wcS\" data-anker=\"Z0b2dbba84cd425084862e30873efee1a\">the cell</a> to repair, leading to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=VP0GdT&anker=Zb3483fa4a700b90a3cd8ccb27fb6b899\" data-learningcard-id=\"VP0GdT\" data-anker=\"Zb3483fa4a700b90a3cd8ccb27fb6b899\" data-section-id=\"bFXHg-\" data-sememe-id=\"ntX7V-\">cell death</a>.<br><br><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=oo001S&anker=Za0493ec3415ed9dd482e76317fbd9b9a\" data-learningcard-id=\"oo001S\" data-anker=\"Za0493ec3415ed9dd482e76317fbd9b9a\" data-section-id=\"DLc1-10\" data-sememe-id=\"Xqb9Cu\">DNA</a> double-strand breaks may also cause malignant transformation due to faulty cell repair, leading to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=iT0Jq2&anker=Zc0da5e32087bb9fdebbaad4515b11425\" data-learningcard-id=\"iT0Jq2\" data-anker=\"Zc0da5e32087bb9fdebbaad4515b11425\" data-section-id=\"Hl0KyT\" data-sememe-id=\"vMbAq8\">leukemia</a> (e.g., <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=iT0Jq2&anker=Zdf106029b619b896fe5d8c0363d4258b\" data-learningcard-id=\"iT0Jq2\" data-anker=\"Zdf106029b619b896fe5d8c0363d4258b\" data-section-id=\"Hl0KyT\" data-sememe-id=\"fwbkRD\">AML</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jT0_q2&anker=Z2864a45f3480a8418833d334d4601008\" data-learningcard-id=\"jT0_q2\" data-anker=\"Z2864a45f3480a8418833d334d4601008\" data-sememe-id=\"kP0mUT\">CLL</a>), <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Vg0G82&anker=Z94e9bb965c06456f89b4f65bd35ad270\" data-learningcard-id=\"Vg0G82\" data-anker=\"Z94e9bb965c06456f89b4f65bd35ad270\" data-section-id=\"Fecg0b0\" data-sememe-id=\"_705oh\">papillary thyroid cancer</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HQ0Kxf&anker=Z8ff05dcf1560740b28f49573a0389d8f\" data-learningcard-id=\"HQ0Kxf\" data-anker=\"Z8ff05dcf1560740b28f49573a0389d8f\" data-section-id=\"JHXsrz\" data-sememe-id=\"h7aclN\">osteosarcoma</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=6S0j0f&anker=Z9361cc494b992f190ed993d53ccbc645\" data-learningcard-id=\"6S0j0f\" data-anker=\"Z9361cc494b992f190ed993d53ccbc645\" data-section-id=\"az0Qri\" data-sememe-id=\"5dXiqC\">liver angiosarcoma</a> later in life.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_591086ec5dc90.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>The radiosensitivity of cells varies with cell cycle phase. The image here shows the phases in which radiation results in chromosome aberration (yellow), apoptosis (blue), or mitotic arrest (green).</p><p>Cells in the G2 and M phase demonstrate the highest radiosensitivity, whereas cells in the G1 and S phases generally show radioresistance.</p></div></div></div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>Formation of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=DF0143&anker=Z436c0f227b9f4b107dbce1103b9732b5\" data-learningcard-id=\"DF0143\" data-anker=\"Z436c0f227b9f4b107dbce1103b9732b5\" data-section-id=\"iQdJDp0\" data-sememe-id=\"MRXMnB\">DNA crosslinks</a> is the mechanism by which <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4m03fg&anker=Zb2e2f957b1930d98bb98637139b5a418\" data-learningcard-id=\"4m03fg\" data-anker=\"Zb2e2f957b1930d98bb98637139b5a418\" data-section-id=\"4W13lf0\" data-sememe-id=\"WkaP5k\">alkylating chemotherapeutic agents</a> (e.g., <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4m03fg&anker=Zaad24cb56b33896890f9ae55757c4363\" data-learningcard-id=\"4m03fg\" data-anker=\"Zaad24cb56b33896890f9ae55757c4363\" data-section-id=\"4W13lf0\" data-sememe-id=\"ekax5k\">cyclophosphamide</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4m03fg&anker=Z74afd3bd88c06f8c6f2884aa73f0539b\" data-learningcard-id=\"4m03fg\" data-anker=\"Z74afd3bd88c06f8c6f2884aa73f0539b\" data-section-id=\"4W13lf0\" data-sememe-id=\"fkakMk\">busulfan</a>) destroy malignant cells. The presence of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=DF0143&anker=Z436c0f227b9f4b107dbce1103b9732b5\" data-learningcard-id=\"DF0143\" data-anker=\"Z436c0f227b9f4b107dbce1103b9732b5\" data-section-id=\"iQdJDp0\" data-sememe-id=\"MRXMnB\">DNA crosslinks</a> results in impaired <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ko0U1S&anker=Zf242ab2ee618bfce0bc6dc3d31a33740\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ko0U1S\" data-anker=\"Zf242ab2ee618bfce0bc6dc3d31a33740\" data-sememe-id=\"WJbPGu\">DNA replication</a> of the malignant cells. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4m03fg&anker=Zb2e2f957b1930d98bb98637139b5a418\" data-learningcard-id=\"4m03fg\" data-anker=\"Zb2e2f957b1930d98bb98637139b5a418\" data-section-id=\"4W13lf0\" data-sememe-id=\"WkaP5k\">Alkylating agents</a> are used for a wide variety of malignancies, including <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=H50Klg&anker=Zd1d827339fe27f2c22ea5827f5f0e60c\" data-learningcard-id=\"H50Klg\" data-anker=\"Zd1d827339fe27f2c22ea5827f5f0e60c\">brain tumors</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=iT0Jq2&anker=Zc0da5e32087bb9fdebbaad4515b11425\" data-learningcard-id=\"iT0Jq2\" data-anker=\"Zc0da5e32087bb9fdebbaad4515b11425\" data-section-id=\"Hl0KyT\" data-sememe-id=\"vMbAq8\">leukemias</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z2586a20a2f640af294a4d86b9f8439d0\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z2586a20a2f640af294a4d86b9f8439d0\" data-section-id=\"azXQr00\" data-sememe-id=\"7RX4oB\">lymphomas</a>.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_5ea995082b7e4.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>Overview of common chemotherapeutic agents and their molecular targets.</p></div></div></div>",
      "hint": "External beam radiation is a form of ionizing radiation that causes apoptosis of cancer cells through the induction of DNA double-strand breaks.",
