    {
      "text": "A 51-year-old woman reports a 3-month history of increasing fatigue and weight gain. She has no new pain or dysphagia. Her temperature is 36.7°C, her blood pressure is 115/74 mm Hg, her heart rate is 55 beats per minute, and her respiratory rate is 12 breaths per minute. Her medical history is significant for squamous-cell carcinoma of the tongue base, which was treated 2 years ago with concurrent chemoradiation to the tongue and cervical lymph nodes.\nWhat is the most appropriate next step in the care of this patient?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Perform a swallow study using diatrizoic acid"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Check the thyroid-stimulating hormone level"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Obtain a radioiodine-uptake scan of the neck"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Check calcium and vitamin D levels"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Measure the serum calcitonin level"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 2,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>A swallow study is indicated in a patient with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=D501mg&anker=Zd2d195657240f493374e95e2b75cc8cf\" data-learningcard-id=\"D501mg\" data-anker=\"Zd2d195657240f493374e95e2b75cc8cf\" data-section-id=\"-ZXDV9\" data-sememe-id=\"IQ0Yxf\">dysphagia</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) CORRECT:</h4>Radiation is a mainstay of treatment for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ts068h&anker=Zeca9293497f7aff515bf436a04e854d8\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ts068h\" data-anker=\"Zeca9293497f7aff515bf436a04e854d8\">head and neck cancers</a>, but it is associated with late toxicities, including <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=cg0a82&anker=Z3fd41eef8b8ce3cec9c7eda727b6d1ce\" data-learningcard-id=\"cg0a82\" data-anker=\"Z3fd41eef8b8ce3cec9c7eda727b6d1ce\" data-sememe-id=\"CP0qST\">hypothyroidism</a> at a median of 1.5 years after treatment. Nearly half of patients receiving <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=L50wkg&anker=Zd120147b0e92bb22668d9e60dfbdc88b\" data-learningcard-id=\"L50wkg\" data-anker=\"Zd120147b0e92bb22668d9e60dfbdc88b\" data-sememe-id=\"-L0DZS\">radiotherapy</a> for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ts068h&anker=Zeca9293497f7aff515bf436a04e854d8\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ts068h\" data-anker=\"Zeca9293497f7aff515bf436a04e854d8\">head and neck cancers</a> develop <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=cg0a82&anker=Z3fd41eef8b8ce3cec9c7eda727b6d1ce\" data-learningcard-id=\"cg0a82\" data-anker=\"Z3fd41eef8b8ce3cec9c7eda727b6d1ce\" data-sememe-id=\"CP0qST\">hypothyroidism</a> within 5 years. The <span data-sememe-id=\"ua1pm20\">threshold dose</span> of radiation leading to this condition is unknown. The National Comprehensive Cancer Network guidelines recommend monitoring <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=AT0Rt2&anker=Zbc03040ec893396d15c13d0b69e3dba4\" data-learningcard-id=\"AT0Rt2\" data-anker=\"Zbc03040ec893396d15c13d0b69e3dba4\" data-section-id=\"XK19U30\" data-sememe-id=\"jKa_Tl\">thyroid-stimulating hormone</a> levels every 6 to 12 months after neck <span data-sememe-id=\"ta1Xm20\">irradiation</span>.<br><br><span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Key learning point:</b></span> Treatment of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ts068h&anker=Zeca9293497f7aff515bf436a04e854d8\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ts068h\" data-anker=\"Zeca9293497f7aff515bf436a04e854d8\">head and neck cancers</a> with radiation can lead to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=cg0a82&anker=Z3fd41eef8b8ce3cec9c7eda727b6d1ce\" data-learningcard-id=\"cg0a82\" data-anker=\"Z3fd41eef8b8ce3cec9c7eda727b6d1ce\" data-sememe-id=\"CP0qST\">hypothyroidism</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>A <span data-sememe-id=\"GN1Bch0\">radioiodine</span>-uptake scan is used to detect thyroiditis or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=bg0HF2&anker=Z7efc7350132a2f2a3e4cc7763e7f07f8\" data-learningcard-id=\"bg0HF2\" data-anker=\"Z7efc7350132a2f2a3e4cc7763e7f07f8\" data-section-id=\"Ol1ICS0\" data-sememe-id=\"9P0NST\">hyperthyroidism</a>, not <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=cg0a82&anker=Z3fd41eef8b8ce3cec9c7eda727b6d1ce\" data-learningcard-id=\"cg0a82\" data-anker=\"Z3fd41eef8b8ce3cec9c7eda727b6d1ce\" data-sememe-id=\"CP0qST\">hypothyroidism</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ts068h&anker=Zeca9293497f7aff515bf436a04e854d8\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ts068h\" data-anker=\"Zeca9293497f7aff515bf436a04e854d8\">Head and neck cancers</a> are known to cause paraneoplastic <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=UI0bXh&anker=Ze68781981f01766eb6f2131c36ab51f2\" data-learningcard-id=\"UI0bXh\" data-anker=\"Ze68781981f01766eb6f2131c36ab51f2\" data-sememe-id=\"JqYszJ\">hypercalcemia</a>, but the absence of new local symptoms makes this unlikely.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>Serum <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Hg0K92&anker=Z8f09b075f4d87191d15890436cb2a4a5\" data-learningcard-id=\"Hg0K92\" data-anker=\"Z8f09b075f4d87191d15890436cb2a4a5\" data-section-id=\"rTcfHb0\" data-sememe-id=\"OG0Izh\">calcitonin</a> levels are used to investigate <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Vg0G82&anker=Zf00b81414d54431f10bce7cd9fff4d3b\" data-learningcard-id=\"Vg0G82\" data-anker=\"Zf00b81414d54431f10bce7cd9fff4d3b\" data-section-id=\"Fecg0b0\" data-sememe-id=\"HQVKx80\">medullary thyroid carcinoma</a>, not <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z17c54b50884f6ae691e10c71ea7eccb6\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z17c54b50884f6ae691e10c71ea7eccb6\" data-section-id=\"azXQr00\" data-sememe-id=\"prXLRz\">squamous-cell carcinoma</a>.</div>",
